      • fetchFormInfo

        public java.util.ArrayList<XYDataPointObject> fetchFormInfo(int uid)
                                                     throws java.sql.SQLException
        Helper method used to fetch form objects associated by a user's id. The form object is created by querying the database to fetch all form objects for a particular user and is returned as a set of 2 XYDataPointObjects that includes the id (integer) of the form as well as the name (string).
        Parameters:
        uid -
        Returns:
        Form info as XYDataPointObject
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • writeFormInfo

        public int writeFormInfo(int uid,
                java.lang.String form_name)
                  throws java.sql.SQLException
        This method is called from the 'Save data request' button on the data request .jsp page. It takes the relevant data request info and stores it in the MySQL database. The database used two tables: one stores each form for all users using a unique form name and the user's ID and the other table stores the parameters of the form with the associated form id.
        Parameters:
        uid -
        form_name -
        Returns:
        Integer value representing the form id as it appears in the database
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • writeFormData

        public void writeFormData(int form_id,
                 java.util.ArrayList<XYDataPointObject> keyVals)
                   throws java.sql.SQLException
        This method handles taking request parameters and saving them to the SQL form database. While not the most efficient way to insert (row x row) the data request will never be large enough to really necessitate the use of a more efficient insert.
        Parameters:
        form_id - The auto-incremented valued obtained from writeFormInfo()
        keyVals - The parameters to be saved to the db
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
        See Also:
        writeFormInfo()

      • deleteForm

        public void deleteForm(int form_id)
                throws java.sql.SQLException
        Helper method used to delete saved forms from the db. The method first deletes the key/value parameters from form_data_key_val table and then removes the form id and name entry from form_info table
        Parameters:
        form_id - The int id of the form to be deleted
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
